# GPU-fit tuning: Qwen3-Coder-Next UD-Q5_K_M on Strix Halo (MACHINE=strixhalo).
#
# Sourced by the launchers AFTER models/qwen3-coder-next.env and BEFORE
# profiles/strixhalo/default.env.
#
# NO --n-cpu-moe HERE (the old value of 40 was a pessimization): expert offload
# only helps discrete cards whose VRAM can't hold the experts. On Strix Halo's
# unified memory the whole model already sits in the same pool the GPU computes
# from, so offloading experts just moves their FFN math onto slower CPU threads.
# (Community Strix Halo numbers for this model: ~40+ t/s TG on Vulkan, all-GPU.)
#
# Memory budget vs ~108 GiB GTT (KV math verified 2026-07-17: only 12 of 48
# layers are full attention, 2 KV heads x head_dim 256 -> 12,288 KV elements
# per token; DeltaNet layers keep a small constant F32 state instead of KV):
#   weights 55.2 GiB + 256K KV at q8_0 (~3.2 GiB) + compute buffers (~2 GiB)
#   ~= 60 GiB  ->  native-max context fits with ~48 GiB to spare.
# For >256K use the qwen3-coder-next-1m config (YaRN-gated) instead of raising
# CTX_SIZE here -- beyond 262144 without rope scaling the model degrades.
: "${CTX_SIZE:=262144}"
